<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,761,1364]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,671,761,788]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">
General description of Japanese 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[538,664,761,788]" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Eloeophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[538,664,761,788]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Eloeophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[677,738,761,787]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Head</emphasis>
. Eye dichoptic; anterior part of vertex about 1/3 width of head. Rostrum about half length of eye in lateral view. Antenna 16-segmented; scape cylindrical, about twice as long as pedicel; pedicel globular; flagellomeres covered with pubescence and verticils. Palpus 5-segmented.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,761,1364]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis box="[199,280,869,895]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Thorax</emphasis>
. Prescutum bearing distinct prescutal pit. Tuberculate pit absent. Pleuron with meron small; mid and hind coxae close to each other. Wing often sparsely or heavily spotted. M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[989,1014,924,938]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">1+2</subScript>
forked. Cell bm with supernumerary m-cu near middle. Legs with tibial spurs 1 + 2 + 2. Halter usually 0.7 times as long as thorax or shorter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,761,1364]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis box="[199,313,977,1003]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Male terminalia with tergite 9 not separated from sternite 9. Gonocoxite with outer and inner gonostylus. Outer gonostylus sclerotized, usually flattened dorsoventrally. Inner gonostylus freshly. Parameres extending medially, fused with each other at center, forming bridge. Mesal-apical lobe of paramere bare at tip. Lateral apodeme of lower shelf about as long as lower shelf. Ovipositor (
<figureCitation box="[893,981,1085,1111]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1599,1623]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,201,1547]" captionTargetId="figure-16@2.[151,1435,179,1574]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eloeophila amamiana (Alexander, 1956). A. habitus, lateral view; B. wing; C. male terminalia, dorsal view; D. outer gonostylus, ventral view; E. aedeagal complex, dorsal view; F. same, lateral view (left = dorsal); G. paramere, dorsal surface; H. female terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars: A–B, 2 mm; C–H, 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: ad, aedeagus; av, apodeme of vesica; cr, cercus; hv, hypogynial valve; ig, inner gonostylus; lp, lateral apodeme; ls, lower shelf; outer gonostylus; pm, paramere; s m-cu, supernumerary m-cu; sX, sternite X; tX, tergite X; vs, vesica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5057237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5057237/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
) with cercus longer than tergite 10. Hypogynial valve longer than sternite 8.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="426" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,761,1364]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1157,1183]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[324,447,1157,1183]" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Eloeophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[324,447,1157,1183]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Eloeophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<emphasis box="[603,707,1157,1183]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Idioptera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Macquart, J." box="[717,897,1157,1184]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" refId="ref18658" refString="Macquart, J. (1834) Histoire naturelle des Insectes. Dipteres. Ouvrage accompagne de planches. Tome premier. Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret, Paris, 578 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 14274" type="book" year="1834">
Macquart, 
<quantity box="[841,897,1157,1183]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.65836" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" unit="in" value="1834.0">1834</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
in terms of having a supernumerary m-cu, but differenciated from the genus by the following characters: outer gonostylus of male terminalia heavily sclerotized, dark, usually flattened dorsoventrally, tip usually pointed (not heavily sclerotized, almost as pale as inner gonostylus, not flattened dorsoventrally, obtuse at tip in 
<emphasis box="[692,796,1265,1291]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Idioptera</emphasis>
). In general appearance and structure of male terminalia, this genus resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Alexander, 1956 b" authorityName="Alexander" authorityYear="1956" box="[389,766,1301,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Afrolimnophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[389,559,1301,1327]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Afrolimnophila</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Alexander, C. P." box="[564,766,1301,1328]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" pagination="129 - 380" refId="ref18376" refString="Alexander, C. P. (1956 b) Tipulidae. Ruwenzori Expedition 1934 - 35, 1, 129 - 380." type="journal article" year="1956">Alexander, 1956b</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but species of the latter genus do not have a supernumerary m-cu. (rarely the crossvein present, but differing in the structure of the male terminalia).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
